'''Lawangan''' is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language of the [[East Barito languages|East Barito]] group. It is spoken by about 100,000 [[Lawangan people]] (one of the [[Dayak people]]s) living in the central [[Kalimantan]], [[Indonesia]]. Lawangan has a high degree of dialectal diversity.

